.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Code: \[la]https://github.com/sunaku/binman\[ra]
.IP \(bu 2
Docs: \[la]https://sunaku.github.io/binman/man\[ra]
.IP \(bu 2
Bugs: \[la]https://github.com/sunaku/binman/issues\[ra]
.RE
.TH binman \- manpages from comment headers
.PP
binman generates manual pages from comment headers in your scripts so that you
can keep your documentation and implementation together, in the same file, for
easy maintenance.  But keeping them apart, in separate files, is supported too.
.PP
[Obligatory screen\-shot of 
.BR binman (1) 
in action!](EXAMPLE.png)
.SH Features
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Direct support for any scripting language that has multi\-line comments or
uses \fB\fC#\fR for single\-line comments: Ruby, Perl, PHP, Python, R, Node.js,
Elixir, Make, Tcl, AWK, sed, all UNIX shells, Windows PowerShell and more!
.IP \(bu 2
Individual commands for manual page extraction, conversion, and display.
.IP \(bu 2
Accessible from the command line and also from within Ruby, as a library.
.IP \(bu 2
Implemented in roughly 165 statement lines (SLOC) of pure Ruby code! :\-)
.RE
.SH Examples
.PP
Here are some examples of HTML manual page \fIsets\fP generated by 
.BR binman-rake (1):
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\[la]https://sunaku.github.io/dasht/man\[ra]
.IP \(bu 2
\[la]https://sunaku.github.io/tork/man\[ra]
.IP \(bu 2
\[la]https://sunaku.github.io/binman/man\[ra]
.IP \(bu 2
\[la]https://sunaku.github.io/md2man/man\[ra]
.RE
.PP
For examples of input and output files, see "Generating manual pages" below.
.SH Installation
.PP
You need to have Ruby 1.8.7 or 1.9.2 or newer installed on your system.
.SS For users
.PP
If you only want to view pre\-built manual pages:
.PP
.RS
.nf
gem install binman
.fi
.RE
.PP
If you also want to build your own manual pages:
.PP
.RS
.nf
gem install md2man \-v '~> 5.0'
.fi
.RE
.SS For developers
.PP
.RS
.nf
git clone https://github.com/sunaku/binman
cd binman
bundle install
bundle exec binman \-\-help # run it directly
bundle exec rake \-\-tasks  # packaging tasks
.fi
.RE
.SH Usage
.PP
binman is used primarily in two ways:
.nr step0 0 1
.RS
.IP \n+[step0]
Generate manual pages at "compile time" and ship them with your scripts.
.IP \n+[step0]
Generate manual pages at "run time" so that your scripts are standalone.
.RE
.SS At compile time
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Run \fB\fCbinman\-rake\fR to generate manual pages for all of your \fB\fCbin/*\fR scripts.
.RE
.PP
Optionally, for more control over the generation of your manual pages:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Run \fB\fCbinman text\fR to extract manual page text from a specified script.
.IP \(bu 2
Run \fB\fCbinman roff\fR to generate a UNIX manual page from a specified script.
.IP \(bu 2
Run \fB\fCbinman html\fR to generate a HTML manual page from a specified script.
.RE
.SS At run time
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Run \fB\fCbinman show\fR to unconditionally display the manual page, which may
have already been generated at "compile time", for a specified script.
.IP \(bu 2
Run \fB\fCbinman help\fR to display the manual page, which may have already been
generated, at "compile time", for a specified script only when either \fB\fC\-h\fR
or \fB\fC\-\-help\fR is found among the optionally supplied command line arguments.
.PP
This is an easy way to add help flags to your script without having to
write any code to parse command\-line options, portably launch 
.BR man (1),
or fall back to displaying an HTML or text version of the manual page.
.PP
See "Displaying manual pages" below for examples in various languages.
.RE
.SS Writing manual pages
.PP
Read all of 
.BR md2man (5) 
and the "Leading comment headers" section in 
.BR binman (1).
For examples, see the scripts linked under "Generating manual pages" below.
.SS Generating manual pages
.PP
Here are some real\-life examples of generating manual pages using 
.BR binman (1):
.PP
Note that 
.BR binman-rake (1) 
abstracts away all of the complexity you see below!
.RS
